  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">William Lloyd Garrison writes that the prospects for the Liberator newspaper are now &quot;bright and cheering.&quot; He comments on the effect of the circular &quot;Thoughts [on African Colonization].&quot; He also discusses the weakness of Ralph R. Gurley&apos;s attack. James Cropper of Liverpool denounced the Colonization Society. Garrison rejoices that Rev. Jocelyn will be with them in Providence.</subfield>
